reviews.text: A place of sadness and frustration. Not so much the long delays, but the constant small delays, followed by squeezing onto a packed train (on weekdays) which has been heavily populated at New Street during the delay (if heading south). The northbound journey is more pleasant.

Open on Saturday. 
Excellent staff.
Great programs for trains. 
The perfect choice to go to Cadbury world.
Pretty decent for a suburban station.
Not the best experience. Wanted to buy a ticket and was spoken to rudely by a member of staff! Really need to work on providing good customer service!

Surprisingly busy for a small station 
But it does the job 
Walking to the station doesn't even look like a one as tickets machine is outside and small shop like counter
